abstract: "Cats" star Jason Derulo has hit back at critics who have slammed the film adaptation of the hit stage musical, calling the movie "an incredible, brave piece of art".
snippet: "Cats" star Jason Derulo has hit back at critics who have slammed the film adaptation of the hit stage musical, calling the movie "an incredible, brave piece of art".
lead_paragraph: LONDON — "Cats" star Jason Derulo has hit back at critics who have slammed the film adaptation of the hit stage musical, calling the movie "an incredible, brave piece of art".
headline_main: 'Cats' Star Derulo Says 'Reviews Don't Matter' After Critics Claw Musical Film
headline_print_headline: 'Cats' Star Derulo Says 'Reviews Don't Matter' After Critics Claw Musical Film

abstract: Russia must keep to schedule on implementing the Nord Stream 2 gas pipeline link to Europe, a senior Russian senator told state news agency RIA on Saturday, after pipe-laying was suspended due to U.S. sanctions.
snippet: Russia must keep to schedule on implementing the Nord Stream 2 gas pipeline link to Europe, a senior Russian senator told state news agency RIA on Saturday, after pipe-laying was suspended due to U.S. sanctions.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — Russia must keep to schedule on implementing the Nord Stream 2 gas pipeline link to Europe, a senior Russian senator told state news agency RIA on Saturday, after pipe-laying was suspended due to U.S. sanctions.
headline_main: Russia Must Press on With Nord Stream 2 Gas Line to Europe: Russian Senator
headline_print_headline: Russia Must Press on With Nord Stream 2 Gas Line to Europe: Russian Senator

abstract: Benefits were held for Robert F. Kennedy Human Rights, New York Botanical Garden and the Metropolitan Museum of Art.
snippet: Benefits were held for Robert F. Kennedy Human Rights, New York Botanical Garden and the Metropolitan Museum of Art.
lead_paragraph: Robert F. Kennedy Human Rights held an awards dinner at the New York Hilton Midtown on Dec. 12. The New York Botanical Garden held a winter ball on Dec. 13. And the Metropolitan Museum of Art celebrated new acquisitions on Dec. 12.

abstract: Readers across the country told us how they were affected by the decline of local news: “Our community does not know itself.”
snippet: Readers across the country told us how they were affected by the decline of local news: “Our community does not know itself.”
lead_paragraph: City Council and school board meetings. Small-town sports and politics. Local government corruption.

abstract: A Pakistani anti-terrorism court on Saturday sentenced a  liberal scholar and former university lecturer to death on blasphemy charges.
snippet: A Pakistani anti-terrorism court on Saturday sentenced a  liberal scholar and former university lecturer to death on blasphemy charges.
lead_paragraph: ISLAMABAD — A Pakistani anti-terrorism court on Saturday sentenced a liberal scholar and former university lecturer to death on blasphemy charges.
headline_main: Pakistan Court Hands Down Death Sentence to Scholar Accused of Blasphemy
headline_print_headline: Pakistan Court Hands Down Death Sentence to Scholar Accused of Blasphemy

abstract: A company that operates ships laying sections of a new German-Russian pipeline said Saturday it is suspending the work after U.S. President Donald Trump signed legislation threatening sanctions.
snippet: A company that operates ships laying sections of a new German-Russian pipeline said Saturday it is suspending the work after U.S. President Donald Trump signed legislation threatening sanctions.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — A company that operates ships laying sections of a new German-Russian pipeline said Saturday it is suspending the work after U.S. President Donald Trump signed legislation threatening sanctions.
headline_main: Firm Suspends Nord Stream 2 Pipeline Work Over US Sanctions
headline_print_headline: Firm Suspends Nord Stream 2 Pipeline Work Over US Sanctions

abstract: Amid a crisis in local news, eight journalists who left newsrooms in 2019 reflect on the stories left in their notebooks. Photographers who also lost their jobs captured them on their former beats.
snippet: Amid a crisis in local news, eight journalists who left newsrooms in 2019 reflect on the stories left in their notebooks. Photographers who also lost their jobs captured them on their former beats.
lead_paragraph: They were experts on New Orleans public schools and Oregon state politics. They shared the news when a popular high school basketball player in Colorado returned to the court after a knee injury, and they helped solve the mystery of a City Hall cake vandalism in Texas. At newspapers big and small — for moments grand and modest — these local newspaper journalists told the stories of their communities.

abstract: While Germany’s Christmas markets are a  favorite among travelers, a little-known market in Transylvania has added sparkle to an ancient city with a German-speaking community.
snippet: While Germany’s Christmas markets are a  favorite among travelers, a little-known market in Transylvania has added sparkle to an ancient city with a German-speaking community.
lead_paragraph: In the cobbled old town of Sibiu, an ancient Transylvanian city in the heart of Romania, a small Christmas market is in full swing, with the sweet scent of mulled wine filling the air and a tall spruce, a tiny ice rink and children’s attractions spreading the holiday spirit.

abstract: China’s repressed Uighurs have long found sanctuary in Turkey. But as the country strengthens ties with China, the Uighurs feel their safe haven shrinking.
snippet: China’s repressed Uighurs have long found sanctuary in Turkey. But as the country strengthens ties with China, the Uighurs feel their safe haven shrinking.
lead_paragraph: ISTANBUL — Six years ago, he fled China’s crackdown on Muslim Uighurs and sought refuge in Turkey, joining a community of fellow exiles. He started a business with his brother, translating and publishing self-help books into their language. His wife got a job as a teacher in a Uighur school where his children began to take classes.
